Backend
This backend powers a dual-panel platform for Users and Food Partners, designed with a modular, scalable, and secure architecture. Both panels operate on separate controllers, routes, and business logic, enabling clean separation of responsibilities and independent feature expansion.

The system is optimized for modern food discovery experiences, combining media-rich content, authentication workflows, and role-based features to support a fast-growing platform.

â­ Key Features
ğŸ”¹ 1. Dual-Panel Backend Architecture

Dedicated backend logic for Users and Food Partners.

Independent controllers, route groups, and validation layers.

Makes the system easy to maintain, scale, and extend in the future.

ğŸ”¹ 2. Secure Authentication & Token Management

JWT Token is mandatory and required for all protected actions.

Ensures secure session control and strict role-based access.

Token-based Forgot Password system:

Issues a secure reset token.

Token is considered valid only after the reset link is clicked.

Follows strong security standards and best practices.

ğŸ”¹ 3. Media Handling System

Reels / Videos processed and optimized through ImageKit for fast delivery.

Images handled through Cloudinary with responsive transformations.

Architecture is ready to migrate to AWS S3, CloudFront, and Lambda for enterprise-level scaling.

ğŸ”¹ 4. Food Partner Capabilities

Complete profile management (update details, change photos, modify information).

Ability to upload promotional reels, images, and business media.

Enhances visibility and builds trust with local users.

ğŸ”¹ 5. User Experience Features

Users can explore restaurants through reels, images, menus, and location data.

Comment system for ratings and interaction.

Can directly contact restaurants or view detailed profiles.

ğŸ”¹ 6. Comment System (Role-Separated)

Different logic for:

User â†’ Restaurant comments

Food Partner â†’ User or platform interactions

Prevents data overlap and ensures clean identity validation.

